{
  "name": "Beacon Of Hope",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "modules/pf1spheres/assets/icons/spheres/light.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>When you place a glow effect on a creature, you may choose to grant that creature a +1 morale bonus on saves against fear. This bonus increases by 1 for every 5 caster levels possessed. You may spend a spell point to create bright light that empowers those within it. All creatures within the area under the effect of a fear effect are allowed a new saving throw at the effect&#8217;s original saving throw to end the effect, if one was originally given.</p>\n<p>So long as a creature is within this area of bright light, whenever they attempt a saving throw vs. a new fear effect, they may roll twice and take the better result.</p>\n",
